Sentencas: Redox stable K2NiF4 type layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-delta(SLFO4-delta) has been prepared and evaluated as anode for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SLFO4 _ 6 shows linear thermal expansion behavior with TEC of 14.3 x 10(-6)K(-1).
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It also demonstrates excellent catalytic activity for various fuels.
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: A scandia stabilized zirconia (ScSZ, 180 mu m) electrolyte supported SOFC with the anode achieves maximum power densities (P-max) of 0.93, 0.76, 0.63, and 0.46 Wcm(-2) at 900-750 degrees C, respectively, in wet H-2.
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: P(max)s of cells supported by 250 mu m ScSZ reach 0.57, 0.60 and 0.50 Wcm(-2) in H-2, H-2 + 50 ppm H2S and propane, respectively, at 800 degrees C. Moreover, the cells show stable power output during similar to 100 h operation at 800 degrees C under 0.7 V in various fuels.
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The P-max at 800 degrees C in wet H-2 even increases by similar to 11% in the subsequent two thermal cyclings, indicating that SLFO4-delta is a promising anode candidate for SOFC with good electro-catalytic activity, high stability and resistance to sulfur and coking.
Titulo: Sulfur tolerant redox stable layered perovskite SrLaFeO4-δ as anode for solid oxide fuel cells
